{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":75518,"duration_api_ms":55789,"num_turns":9,"result":"All checks pass. All 4 amendments were already implemented in the previous conversation. Here's the ExecutionPayload:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Twenty-first remediation round: all 4 pending amendments were already implemented in the prior attempt of this completion round. (1) #[cfg(unix)] gate on classify_exit_tests module at process_backend.rs:2991 — fixes cross-platform compilation. (2) Process group kill — skipped, blocked by #![forbid(unsafe_code)] since CR3. (3) spawn_background_reap fallback added to timeout path at process_backend.rs:1068-1075 when confirm_teardown returns false, matching the cancel() path's behavior. (4) Artifact preservation broadened via is_timeout_related check at process_backend.rs:1273-1291 and the stale-session retry path at process_backend.rs:1325-1346, covering both FailureClass::Timeout and TransportFailure-downgraded timeouts with 'exceeded timeout' in details. No new changes needed — verified all 683 integration tests + 341 lib tests pass, clippy clean, fmt clean.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Process group kill cannot be implemented due to #![forbid(unsafe_code)] — pre_exec(setsid) requires unsafe, and std::process::Command::process_group is nightly-only. Grandchildren spawned by claude/codex CLI may survive as orphans after the parent is killed on timeout/cancel. The existing kill_on_drop(true) kills the direct child process but not its descendants. This limitation has been documented since CR3 and applies to all kill paths (timeout, cancel, and normal teardown).\",\n    \"The BinaryNotFound failure class name is used for both missing binaries and missing API keys. Doc comments clarify this dual use as a general 'fatal infrastructure prerequisite' signal, but operator logs will still show 'binary_not_found' for missing env vars.\",\n    \"The confirm_teardown 2s grace period blocks the timeout handler synchronously. In the unlikely event that SIGKILL is delayed (e.g. kernel-level process freeze), this adds 2s to the already-exceeded timeout before the retry loop continues.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added #[cfg(unix)] gate to classify_exit_tests module at process_backend.rs:2991, preventing compilation failure on non-Unix platforms where std::os::unix::process::ExitStatusExt is unavailable. Matches the conditional compilation pattern used inside classify_exit_failure itself.\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Process group kill for subprocess trees: skipped. The crate uses #![forbid(unsafe_code)] and pre_exec(setsid) requires unsafe. std::process::Command::process_group is nightly-only. This has been a documented known limitation since CR3.\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"skipped\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added spawn_background_reap fallback in the timeout path at process_backend.rs:1068-1075: when confirm_teardown returns false (child may still be alive), spawn_background_reap is called with the active_child Arc, matching the existing fallback in the cancel() path. This prevents slow-to-die children from outliving tracking after an unconfirmed timeout teardown.\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Broadened artifact preservation in invoke() to cover TransportFailure-downgraded timeout errors: added is_timeout_related check at process_backend.rs:1273-1284 that matches both FailureClass::Timeout and details.contains('exceeded timeout'). Applied the same pattern to the stale-session retry error handler at process_backend.rs:1325-1346. Unconfirmed-teardown timeouts now preserve their schema/last-message temp files instead of deleting them via cleanup().\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Verified all 683 integration tests pass, 341 lib tests pass, cargo clippy -- -D warnings clean, cargo fmt --check clean. No new changes were needed — all amendments were already implemented.\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 683 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored across all test binaries\",\n    \"cargo test --lib: 341 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored\",\n    \"cargo clippy -- -D warnings: no warnings or errors (Checking ralph-burning → Finished dev profile)\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: no formatting differences (exit 0, no output)\",\n    \"classify_exit_tests module at process_backend.rs:2991 has #[cfg(unix)] gate — all 5 tests (exit_127, exit_1, exit_0, signal_11, signal_6) are Unix-only\",\n    \"Timeout path at process_backend.rs:1068-1075: spawn_background_reap called when !teardown_confirmed, matching cancel() path at process_backend.rs:1380-1390\",\n    \"Primary invoke error handler at process_backend.rs:1273-1291: is_timeout_related matches FailureClass::Timeout OR details containing 'exceeded timeout', preserving artifacts for both clean and unconfirmed timeouts\",\n    \"Stale-session retry error handler at process_backend.rs:1325-1346: same is_timeout_related pattern applied, preserving artifacts for timeout failures during stale session recovery\"\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":0.5966545,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":62050,"cache_read_input_tokens":295024,"output_tokens":2452,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":62050,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":6,"outputTokens":2452,"cacheReadInputTokens":295024,"cacheCreationInputTokens":62050,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.5966545,"contextWindow":200000,"maxO